I'm very sorry to hear about your situation. When you've had enough of your husband and don't want to continue this relationship, you'll likely need to consider getting a divorce. Divorce is a serious decision and is often not necessary for every relationship problem.

Some steps you may take to prepare for a divorce include:

Seek financial advice and start saving money to cover your own expenses;
Begin to learn more about your rights and obligations in the event of a divorce by reviewing any relevant laws in your jurisdiction;
Take steps to assert your independence - move to your own place, secure employment if you're not already doing so, etc.;
Consider getting legal counsel or a mediator.

Make sure you get the medical, psychological, and legal advice you need. Also, consider contacting organizations that offer support and guidance for separating spouses. Remember, you're not alone in this.

Do not forget to firstly take care of your own physical and mental health. You might find it helpful to seek support from friends, family, or a therapist.
Remember, separation and divorce can be difficult and emotionally challenging. It's important to take your time and make decisions that are right for you.
